com.github.protobufel.crud.el

Class ProtoMessageQueryProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.protobufel.crud.el.ProtoMessageQueryProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    QueryProcessors.IQueryProcessor<Message>

    public final class ProtoMessageQueryProcessor
extends Object
implements QueryProcessors.IQueryProcessor<Message>
    Processes queries, lists of objects, using the EL 3.0 language, including validation and error reporting.

    Also, it allows you to specify your own JavaBeans to be used within the expression, in addition to the predefined ones:

    1. records - the immutable List of the original records
    2. results - the immutable List of the results being produced
    3. record - the current row's Message.Builder, will be in the results
    4. index - the current row's index in the results

    You can also specify the so called empty expression to the Builder to produce the original records.

    In addition, you can add your own QueryProcessors.ValidationListener and QueryProcessors.QueryResultListener.

    If your expression returns null, the current result will be skipped, so this is the way to remove the original record from the results. The QueryProcessors.QueryResultListener.resultAdded(int) allows you to keep track of the being produced results. Initially, the results list is empty; and the result producing loop follows the original records. So, the originals vs the results diffs can be easily and efficiently calculated.

    Author:
    protobufel@gmail.com David Tesler
